{
  "id": "019cfc25-8d0c-7f83-aebe-454e8945e3fe",
  "content": "## SAM2.1 Hydra Config Loading Fix (2025-11-01 test run)\n\nCommit `a1b2252` on `main`.\n\n### Problem\nSAM2's `__init__.py` registers `pkg://sam2` as hydra's config search path via `initialize_config_module(\"sam2\")`. This only finds YAML files at the package root level (`sam2_hiera_s.yaml`, etc.) — these are SAM2 v1 configs. SAM2.1 weights (`sam2.1_hiera_small.pt`) have extra layers (`no_obj_embed_spatial`, `obj_ptr_tpos_proj.weight`, `obj_ptr_tpos_proj.bias`) that don't exist in the v1 model architecture, causing `RuntimeError: Unexpected key(s) in state_dict`.\n\nThe SAM2.1 configs that match these weights live in `configs/sam2.1/` inside the package but aren't on hydra's search path.\n\n### Fix\nIn `load_sam2_model()`, clear the existing hydra global state and re-initialize with `initialize_config_dir` pointing directly at the `sam2/configs/sam2.1/` directory. The config map values (`sam2.1_hiera_s`, etc.) match the YAML filenames in that directory.\n\n### Fragility note\nThis fix clears and replaces SAM2's own hydra initialization. It works because `import sam2` has already run (top-level import) and `build_sam2_video_predictor` uses `compose()` which picks up whichever hydra context is active. If SAM2 upgrades its package to register `configs/` properly, this workaround should be removed.\n\n### How to reproduce\n```bash\ncd repos/dorea/scripts\npython 03_run_sam2.py --date 2025-11-01\n```\nBefore fix: `MissingConfigException: Cannot find primary config 'sam2.1_hiera_s'`\nAfter fix: `Loaded checkpoint successfully` → tracking starts.",
  "source_version": "mcp",
